         <abstract>
            <p>Multiple-of-earnings methods are taught in most investment classes. Unfortunately, students find it difficult to determine appropriate P/E ratios and often rely upon published ratios that are based on historical earnings amounts. This paper explains a simple exercise of forecasting P/E ratios for the S&amp;P 500 stock index and for an individual company. A multiple regression model is used with an earnings cycle and interest rates as predictive variables.</p>
